article.headline: Kent State 73, Ohio 60
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- DeAndre Haynes scored 16 points and Nate Gerwig added 15 to lead Kent State to a 73-60 victory over Ohio on Wednesday night. Jay Youngblood had 12 points and Omni Smith 10 for the Golden Flashes (15-6, 9-1), off to their best start in the Mid-American Conference. Sonny Troutman and Whitney Davis each had 12 points, Leon Williams scored 11 and Jerome Tillman had 10 for the Bobcats (12-6, 6-4), who have lost three in a row. The loss was Ohio's third in its last 25 home games. Ahead 35-31 at the half, the Flashes ran off the next five points with Smith hitting a 3-pointer and Haynes making a layup. The Bobcats got as close as 55-50 on Davis' 3-pointer with 11:35 left before Youngblood answered with a 3. The lead never dropped below six points again. Kent State shot 63 percent from the field (17 of 27) in the second half.
